.TH Test-HomebridgeArtifactsGeneration 1 "31 October 2025" "NobleFactor" "Homebridge Artifact Testing"
.SH NAME
Test-HomebridgeArtifactsGeneration \- Automated test for Homebridge artifact and certificate generation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Test-HomebridgeArtifactsGeneration
\fB--location\fR <location> [\fB--template-dir\fR <dir>] [\fB--help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This script compares generated Homebridge artifacts to baseline reference files.
.PP
- The generated YAML file is always './homebridge-<location>.yaml'.
- The baseline YAML file is './test/baseline/homebridge-<location>.yaml'.
- The generated secrets directory is './secrets/<location>'.
- The baseline secrets directory is './test/baseline/<location>'.
- Field-by-field comparisons are performed for certificate artifacts.
- The template directory defaults to '.' but can be overridden.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --location <location>
Location name (e.g., 'fake-wa')
.TP
.B --template-dir <dir>
Directory containing templates (default: '.')
.TP
.B --help
Show usage information
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run the test for location 'fake-wa':
.IP
Test-HomebridgeArtifactsGeneration --location fake-wa
.PP
Override the template directory:
.IP
Test-HomebridgeArtifactsGeneration --location fake-wa --template-dir ./templates
